casebody.data:
Maxwell D. KAMPERT, Respondent,
v.
DIRECTOR OF REVENUE, Appellant. WD 81081 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: August 14, 2018 Jeffrey S. Eastman, Gladstone, MO, Attorney for Respondent. Joshua D. Hawley, Attorney General, and Morgan L. Brewington, Special Assistant Attorney General, Jefferson City, MO, Attorneys for Appellant. Before Special Division: Zel M. Fischer, Special Judge, and Mark D. Pfeiffer and Gary D. Witt, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

The Director of Revenue of the State of Missouri appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Platte County, Missouri, ordering the Director to remove the administrative revocation from Mr. Maxwell Kampert's driving record and to reinstate Mr. Kampert's driver's license. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. We affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
